I"*<h1 id="gravity-alumni">Gravity Alumni</h1>

<p>Membership to the Gravity Group is contingent on a selective and rigorous apprenticeship program that strengthens mathematical methods (dimensional analysis, dynamical systems, special functions, and diffential geometry) and soft research skills (writing, LaTeX). All members are required to take General Relativity as one of their electives. Students work on research projects that develop strong proficiency in Mathematica and/or Python, and are expected to submit papers to peer-reviewed SPP conference proceedings. A lively <i> Monday Journal Club </i> is conducted that keeps us abreast on the latest research developments, while also developing students’ critical thinking, public speaking, and their ability to think on their feet. A Crazy These activities develop the skills that help ensure success in a wide variety of careers.</p>

